ND Western Chief Executive Officer, Eberechukwu Oji, says indigenous companies stand as a catalyst for the growth of the Nigerian economy. He spoke ahead of sixth edition of the Sub Saharan Africa International Exhibition and Conference (SAIPEC) next month, where he will be sharing his ideas on strategies in harnessing Nigeria’s oil and gas potentials. According to him, ND Western has a significant asset base in the Nigerian oil and gas value chain with 45% interest on OML 34 in the Niger Delta basin. How To Stop Soot Pollution ‘How Oil Production Underperformance Is Affecting Nigeria,… He added: “I will be speaking on collaboration very strongly at SAIPEC 2022. We need to shift our mindset off competitions and start focusing more on collaboration. There has to be competition, but collaboration is what we need to maximise the potentials of the oil and gas industry and value creation for Nigeria. Nobody will come and develop Nigeria better than we Nigerians.” ND Western is a Nigerian indigenous company with 10 years operational excellence in Niger Delta. The company is a Platinum Sponsor at SAIPEC 2022, and will be speaking as part of the Independents in Africa panel session on day one.